in, R.M., Enhancement of cumulus clouds over deforested lands in Amazonia (1995) Bull Am Meteorol Soc, 76, pp. 1801-1805; Wang, J., Chagnon, F.J.F., Williams, E.R., Betts, A.K., Renno, N.O., Machado, L.A.T., Bisht, G., Bras, L.R., Impact of deforestation in the Amazon basin on cloud climatology (2009) Proc Natl Acad Sci U S A, 106, pp. 3670-3674; Andreae, M.O., Rosenfeld, D., Artaxo, P., Costa, A.A., Frank, G.P., Longo, K.M., Silva-Dias, M.A.F., Smoking rain clouds over the Amazon (2004) Science, 303, pp. 1337-1342; Nepstad, D.C., Tohver, I.M., Ray, D., Moutinho, P., Cardinot, G., Mortality of large trees and lianas following experimental drought in an Amazon forest (2007) Ecology, 88, pp. 2259-2269. , doi:10.1890/06-1046.1; Brando, P.M., Nepstad, D.C., Davidson, E.A., Trumbore, S.E., Ray, D., Camargo, P., Drought effects on litterfall, wood production and belowground carbo cycling in an Amazon forest: results of a throughfall reduction experiment (2008) Philos Trans R Soc B, 363, pp. 1839-1848. , doi:10.1098/rstb.2007.0031; Fisher, R.A., Williams, M., da Costa, A.L., Malhi, Y., da Costa, R.F., Almeida, S., Meir, P., The response of an eastern Amazonian rain forest to drought stress: results and modelling analyses from a through-fall exclusion experiment (2007) Glob Change Biol, 13, pp. 2361-2378. , doi:10. 1111/j.1365-2486.2007.01417.x; Meir, P., Metcalfe, D.B., Costa, A.C.L., Fisher, R.A., The fate of assimilated carbon during drought: impacts on respiration in Amazon rainforests (2008) Philos Trans R Soc B, 363, pp. 1849-1855. , doi:10.1098/rstb. 2007.0021; Phillips, O.L., Martinez, R.V., Arroyo, L., Baker, T.R., Killeen, T., Lewis, S.L., Malhi, Y., Vargas, P.N., Increasing dominance of large lianas in Amazonian forests (2002) Nature, 418, pp. 770-774; Phillips, O.L., Martinez, R.V., Mendoza, A.M., Baker, T.R., Vargas, P.N., Large lianas as hyperdynamic elements of the tropical forest canopy (2005) Ecology, 86, pp. 1250-2125; Marengo, J.A., Nobre, C.A., Tomasella